## Common Commands

```bash
# Dependency management
uv sync                          # Install/sync all dependencies
uv add <package>                 # Add a new dependency
uv run <command>                 # Run a command in the virtual environment

# Testing
uv run pytest                    # Run all tests
uv run pytest -m "not slow"      # Skip slow tests
uv run pytest --cov              # Run with coverage

# Linting
uv run pre-commit run --all-files

# Training (example)
# uv run accelerate launch src/train.py --config configs/train.yaml

# Evaluation
bash scripts/demo_eval.sh        # Demo evaluation (GPT-2 on HellaSwag)
# uv run accelerate launch -m lm_eval run \
#     --model hf \
#     --model_args pretrained=<model> \
#     --tasks <task1>,<task2> \
#     --output_path outputs/

# Docker
bash run.sh                      # Auto-detect GPU and start container
```

## Workspace Structure

This project uses UV workspace (monorepo):

- **Root** (`./`): Main research code in `src/`, shared dependencies
- **`packages/sft`**: SFT training package (customizable)
- **`packages/lm-eval`**: lm-evaluation-harness (submodule, editable)

